Date: 8 Aug 2016
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=20708


Anthrax, France
--------------
Information received on 9 Aug 2016 from Dr Loic Evain, Directeur Général adjoint, CVO, Direction générale de l'alimentation, Ministère de l'Agriculture, de l'Agroalimentaire et de la Forêt, Paris, France

Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Date of start of the event: 22 Jun 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 2 Aug 2016
Report date: 8 Aug 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 9 Aug 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: June 2008
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1 (3): Saint Jean de Basselle, Saint Jean de Basselle, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Jun 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 468 / 11 / 9 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The land where deaths were observed is adjacent to outbreak No. 2. A 6-year-old Charolais cow died suddenly on 22 Jun 2016. Eight other animals died from 18 Jul to 1 Aug 2016. Two animals showing weakening and fever on 1 and 2 Aug 2016 got better under antibiotics.

Outbreak 2 (2): Saint Jean de Basselle, Saint Jean de Basselle, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 118 / 6 / 6 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The 1st animal, a 7-year-old bull, died suddenly (without signs) on 19 Jul 2016, and the other 5 animals died under the same conditions from 24 to 31 Jul 2016.

Outbreak 3 (4): Saint Jean de Basselle, Saint Jean de Basselle, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 40 / 4 / 4 / 1 / 0
Affected population: A 1st death on 28 Jul 2016 then on 1 and 2 Aug 2016, a dead calf and another euthanized.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 626 / 21 / 19 / 1 / 0

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering: Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: Reoccurrence. A history of anthrax cases on these pastures is known.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; Disinfection/Disinfestation; Traceability; Vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Maisons Alfort Animal health laboratory, ANSES (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 5 Aug 2016 / Positive

