Report Type: Follow-up Report No. 2
----------------------------
New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1 (5): Gosselming, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Aug 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 267 / 2 / 2 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The 1st bovine died without presenting symptoms on 10 Aug 2016. Samples were taken on the same day, and the national reference laboratory confirmed the presence of _Bacillus anthracis_. A 2nd bovine died in the same conditions on 15 Aug 2016.

Outbreak 2 (6): Langatte, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Aug 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 214 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A bovine died suddenly. The national reference laboratory confirmed the presence of bacillus anthracis on 18 Aug 2016.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 481 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: Reoccurrence. A history of anthrax cases on these pastures is known.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Maisons Alfort Animal health laboratory, ANSES (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 17 Aug 2016 / Positive
Maisons Alfort Animal health laboratory, ANSES (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 18 Aug 2016 / Positive

