New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1 (7): Langatte, Moselle
Date of start of the outbreak: 18 Aug 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 262 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A dry dairy cow suddenly died on 18 Aug 2016. National Reference Laboratory confirmed the presence of _Bacillus anthracis_ on 23 Aug 2016.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: Reoccurrence. A history of anthrax cases on these pastures is known.

